Ask HN: What should companies be doing with all their empty office space?
text:
My employer has a large office building. Ever since the pandemic, 95% percent of the desks are empty. most of the floors have nobody working on them. it's like the backrooms. 
i was thinking of indoor gardening. bring in some lights and plant trays of seeds.
what are your ideas?

title: Ask HN: When has knowing advanced math been useful in your job/life?
text: I've forgotten almost all of my math since college since I've never needed to use it directly. Maybe the process of learning and studying topics like calculus, discrete logic, stats, and number theory helped hone my thinking powers in some way, but the actual techniques from these courses I've never had to use.

Facebook account blocked and “download your information” returns almost 0
text:
Today Facebook decided to permanently suspend my account? Why? Have no clue? I have been reading their community standards and honestly - can not find anything that I breached ever.

But ok - their platform - their rules! What makes me angry is that when I selected an option to download my information - I got empty folders! 15 years of my digital life: posts, photos, videos - everything has dissapeared in a moment, based on non explained move from an algorithm!

Of course - no appeal or complain possible.

Anyone - any idea if something can be done?

Azure Databricks Pricing Error
text:
The advertised Azure Databricks pricing for NCas_T4_v3 series (NVIDIA T4 GPUs) is incorrect on the website. See https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/pricing/details/databricks/

The advertised prices are much lower than they should be. The basic formula for Databricks is:

(Total Price) = (VM Price) + (DBU Price)

I am not sure if they are billing less than they should be or billing more than they advertise. If you used this series on Azure Databrick you may want to check your billing.
